The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House and Senate Committees on Armed Services and Appropriations, as well as the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House Committee on Foreign Affairs and the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations. The letter discusses the plan to enhance the safety, security, and reliability of the nuclear weapons stockpile of the United States, modernize the nuclear weapons complex, and maintain the delivery platforms for nuclear weapons. The letter emphasizes the importance of maintaining a safe, secure, and effective nuclear arsenal as a deterrent to adversaries and to reassure U.S. allies and security partners. The letter also mentions the administration's commitment to seeking a world without nuclear weapons while acknowledging the need to ensure the safety and effectiveness of the current stockpile.